@startuml
title USF Vision - Layered Authority Model
left to right direction

rectangle "Script-Configured Canonical Definitions\n(mod/modpack, metrics, scales,\nphenomenon_realizer, phenomenon,\nphenomenon_model, capability contracts)" as L1
rectangle "Canonical Runtime Persistence Authority\n(metric state + phenomenon/model authority\nin scale-aware runtime records)" as L2
rectangle "Derived Runtime Projections\n(substrate summaries, realization decisions,\nruntime caches/artifacts)" as L3
rectangle "Capability Platform (Rust/Bevy)\n(channel backends, schedulers, workflows,\nvalidation, fail-fast guards)" as L4

rectangle "Owner Direction" as OD
rectangle "Current Implementation" as CI

OD -[#1E88E5]-> L1 : defines target ontology contract in script language
L1 -[#43A047]-> L2 : is instantiated as canonical runtime authority via bootstrap
L2 -[#43A047]-> L3 : derives runtime projections/caches in deterministic pipelines
L4 -[#43A047]-> L3 : computes projection/update artifacts via capability kernels
L3 -[#8E24AA]-> L2 : feeds bounded reconciliation paths back to canonical runtime state
L1 -[#FB8C00]-> L4 : orchestrates capability usage via typed ctx/channel contracts

CI -[#8E24AA]-> L4 : provides present substrate and implementation constraints
CI -[#8E24AA]-> L2 : provides current persistence mechanics as evidence
OD -[#1E88E5]-> CI : overrides when design intent and implementation diverge

note bottom
Contract split is explicit:
- Owner Direction: target architecture authority.
- Current Implementation: observational evidence only.
end note
@enduml
